The Technical University of Kenya TUK has announced the death of its senior lecturer Dr Gabriel Musungu. The late was a senior lecturer at the Department of Music and Performing Arts and passed away on Monday afternoon. Musungu battled diabetes for many years, a condition that had seen him in and out of the hospital. Three weeks ago, he was hospitalised at MP Shah hospital, due to acute oxygen deficiency. Musungu was the composer of the TUK anthem. The TUK administration said it will miss Musungu's expertise and services immensely.